// place-stable.ipt
// =====================================================================
// A PF2e stable / livery. Reuses people.ipt (stablemaster + customer)
// and prices.ipt. Gives a GM: the stablemaster, the mounts and tack
// for sale or hire with PF2e prices, the state of the yard, a customer,
// and a hook.
//
// Entry table: [@Stable]
//
// Inputs (optional, via API promptValues):
//   prompt1 town  /  prompt2 shopType (display)  /  prompt3 shopName
//
// PF2e prices in COPPER (1 gp = 100 cp). Animal/tack prices from the
// Core Rulebook where confident; (~) marks approximations to verify.

Title: Stable
Use: people.ipt
Use: prices.ipt

Prompt: town {} an unnamed town
Prompt: shopType {} stable
Prompt: shopName {} 

Table: TF-Stable
Set: town={$prompt1}
Set: passedName={$prompt3}
Set: m=[@Markup]
Set: keeper=[@PersonName]
Set: kanc=[@Ancestry]
**[@StableTitle]** *(stable in {$town})*\n&
**[@StableState]**\n&
**Stablemaster:** {$keeper}, a [@PersonDesc] {$kanc} who is [@Personality].\n&
**For sale & hire** ({$markupReason}):\n&
[@StablePriceList]\n&
**In the stalls:** [@StableMounts]\n&
**A customer:** [@StableCustomer]\n&
**{$keeper} says:** "[@StableQuote]"\n&
**Worth noting:** [@StableHook]

Table: StableTitle
[when]{$passedName}=[do][@StableName][else]{$passedName}[end]

Table: StableName
The [@StableNameAdj] [@StableNameNoun]
[@StableKeeperStyle]

// "The Iron Horseshoe" style.
Table: StableNameAdj
Iron
Old
Galloping
Red
Honest
Broad
Dust
Greenfield
Riverside
Crossroads

Table: StableNameNoun
Horseshoe
Stable
Livery
Paddock
Bridle
Mews
Yard
Post

// "Garret's Livery" style — uses a rolled surname for variety.
Table: StableKeeperStyle
[@FamilyName]'s Livery
[@FamilyName]'s Stables

Table: StableState
A tidy yard, tack oiled and stalls mucked
A busy yard, every hand occupied
A run-down place, but the animals look well cared for
A large coaching stable serving the trade road
A modest stable behind the owner's home
The yard's quiet; most mounts are out with their riders

// PF2e Core prices (copper). (~) = approximate, verify.
Table: StablePriceList
- Riding horse ................ [@PricedAs with 2000]\n&
- Warhorse .................... (~) [@PricedAs with 20000]\n&
- Pony ........................ (~) [@PricedAs with 800]\n&
- Mule / donkey ............... [@PricedAs with 600]\n&
- Riding saddle & bridle ...... [@PricedAs with 1000]\n&
- Feed (per day) .............. [@PricedAs with 5]\n&
- Stabling (per night) ........ (~) [@PricedAs with 5]\n&
- Hire a mount (per day) ...... (~) [@PricedAs with 200]

// What's actually in the stalls right now — gives the GM specifics.
Table: StableMounts
{!n=={2+1d3}}[@{$n} StallLine]

Table: StallLine
a [@MountColour] [@MountKind], [@MountTemperament]\n&

Table: MountColour
bay
chestnut
grey
black
dappled
roan
piebald
white

Table: MountKind
riding horse
sturdy pony
heavy draft horse
nervous warhorse
patient mule
spirited courser

Table: MountTemperament
calm and well-trained
skittish around strangers
old but utterly reliable
barely green-broke and a handful
clearly someone's beloved mount, not for sale
favouring one leg — the master swears it's nothing

Table: StableCustomer
{!cust==[@PersonName]}{!canc==[@Ancestry]}{$cust}, a [@PersonDesc] {$canc}, [@StableCustomerDoing]

Table: StableCustomerDoing
haggling hard over the price of a mule
saying a long goodbye to a horse they're selling
demanding to know why their mount isn't ready
inspecting a horse's teeth with the air of an expert
trying to stable a mount they clearly can't afford to keep
asking after a rider who boarded a horse here and vanished

Table: StableQuote
A horse is a partner, not a tool. Treat mine accordingly.
I'll hire you a mount, but I'll want a deposit and a name.
That one's not for sale at any price. Don't ask again.
Feed's extra. Everything's extra. That's how I keep the lights on.
Bring it back in the state you took it, or we'll have words.
I know every horse in this town and most of their riders.
You ride out at dawn? Then you pay tonight.

Table: StableHook
one stall stands conspicuously empty, swept clean and locked
a fine horse was left here a month ago and never collected
the stablemaster is quietly buying mounts faster than they sell
fresh mud and hard-ridden horses suggest someone arrived in a hurry
a brand on one horse matches no local stable or noble house
the master keeps glancing at a sealed letter tucked in the tack

// Standalone name roll (collision-proof, for note titles etc.).
Table: TF-StableName
[@StableName]
